 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of character glyphs and the information needed to describe text fonts and text font families.	 
   </p>
<!-- 2nd edition -->
   <p>
   	This edition incorporates modifications to the previous edition listed below.
   </p>
	<!-- ARM -->
	<p>
	The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been added:
	</p>	
	<ul>
		<li>tr_font_select;</li>
		<li>Annotation_text_character.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>
	The following ARM EXPRESS declarations and interface specifications have been removed:
	</p>	
	<ul>
		<li>USE FROM Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, 
	the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications 
	of the ARM.</p>
 </purpose>

